ChatGPT said:

Your Flutter ElevatedButton code looks mostly correct for sending a password reset email using Firebase Authentication. However, there are a few suggestions for improvement:

✅ 1. Check if student.email is valid:

Make sure student.email is not null or empty, or it will cause an exception.

✅ 2. Improve the ElevatedButton label:

There's a typo: "Chang Password" should be "Change Password".

✅ 3. Add error handling:

Always catch potential errors from Firebase.

✅ Improved Version:

dart
ElevatedButton(
  onPressed: () {
    if (student.email != null && student.email.isNotEmpty) {
      FirebaseAuth.instance.sendPasswordResetEmail(email: student.email).then((_) {
        ScaffoldMessenger.of(context).showMaterialBanner(
          MaterialBanner(
            content: Text("Password reset link sent successfully"),
            actions: [
              TextButton(
                onPressed: () {
                  ScaffoldMessenger.of(context).hideCurrentMaterialBanner();
                },
                child: Text("OK"),
              ),
            ],
          ),
        );
      }).catchError((error) {
        ScaffoldMessenger.of(context).showMaterialBanner(
          MaterialBanner(
            content: Text("Error: ${error.message ?? 'Failed to send email'}"),
            actions: [
              TextButton(
                onPressed: () {
                  ScaffoldMessenger.of(context).hideCurrentMaterialBanner();
                },
                child: Text("Dismiss"),
              ),
            ],
          ),
        );
      });
    } else {
      ScaffoldMessenger.of(context).showMaterialBanner(
        MaterialBanner(
          content: Text("Email is invalid or empty"),
          actions: [
            TextButton(
              onPressed: () {
                ScaffoldMessenger.of(context).hideCurrentMaterialBanner();
              },
              child: Text("OK"),
            ),
          ],
        ),
      );
    }
  },
  child: Text("Change Password"),
),

🔐 Tip:

Firebase will not send an email if the email is not registered in the system — but it won't tell the user to protect privacy. So handle this with a generic message like: "If this email is registered, a reset link has been sent."

Let me know if you're also using a TextField for email input — I can show a version for that too.
